For the sequence, the data must be passed to the right buffer and each buffer must have the right address.</p><p>In this example, the Data has the following format:&nbsp;<br>Pixel exists of 24 Bit (3 x 8 Bit). div.p: Data comes in flat and Buffered (16 Pixel => 384 Bit). Data must be written in a special sequence into the Buffer, so it can be written and read in parallel with the max Bandwidth. For the sequence, the data must be passed to the right buffer and each buffer must have the right address.

In this example, the Data has the following format:
Pixel exists of 24 Bit (3 x 8 Bit). Red ends with 0x1, green ends with 0x3 and blue ends with 0x7.
The higer 4 Bits indicate the SPI Stream, where dhe Data should go to. Because one Matrix is 8x16 Pixels (Width is 8), the indicator gets increased by one every 8 Bytes (64 Bit).
